<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="15" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d15">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source"><persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2" type="from">Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="to">Roosevelt</persName></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d15fn1">Channel of transmission not indicated.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-29">29 June 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>To President from <gloss target="#t_FormerNavalPerson1">former Naval
                                person</gloss> personal and secret. Number 336.</p>
                        <pb facs="0105" n="13" xml:id="pg_13"/>
                        <p>I have now received your 297 and I repeat what I said in my 334 that if
                            you and <gloss target="#t_UncleJ1">Uncle J.</gloss> can fix a meeting
                            together I should no longer deprecate it. On the contrary in view of his
                            attitude I think it important that this contact should be
                            established.</p>
                        <p>I should be very glad to arrange for a meeting between us and our staffs
                            about the end of August in Quebec which I am sure MacKenzie King would
                            welcome. Later on I will put the point to him.</p>
                        <p>Many thanks for your very full message.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>